                     Ʋrine thick and ſtinking. The Pulſe ſmall and deep; there is Bubo's behind the Ears, under the Arm-holes, or in the grom; or elſe Carbuncles or Blew, Reddiſh, or Lived ſpots, the Diſeaſe is dangerous, but 'tis moſt

deadly when no Buboe's come forth, or when they come forth and go in again, or if they the ſpots appear of a Livid or black Colour, 'tis commonly mortal. The Cure.
